content.description: Start about in the middle of Warm-Up Wall, sit start on the low, slopey jugs. Staying inches off the ground, traverse left with them tight heel hooks, and then up to the start holds of The Prow. Finish The Prow.
content.protection: Two pads for finishing on The Prow. This thing is so low that putting a pad beneath you on the traverse would certainly result in dabbing.
content.location: Center of Warm-Up Wall (Porcelain Doll Wall)

content.description: Traverse Horizontals, mellow warm up   If you go out and back give yourself v0+
content.location: start same as the prow and traverse right till your bored or run out of holds

content.description: Sit start on the sloper and crimp, down and right of The Prow (stand start). Move into the Prow and finish.
content.location: Starts to the left of Another Shitty Warmup.

content.description: Start on the left side of the rail to an undercling pinch to the jug.  Move to a crimp or all the way to the top.  Several variations on this one exist.
content.location: The left most route to the right of the tree.  Just right of and on the arete.

content.description:
Start near the warm up flake shaped like this < on the skirt of the wall where you can stand up onto it hands-free. Basically start as far to the right on the slab as you can. Traverse left all the way across the wall, on horizontals, edges, pockets, and eventually jugs. Once you reach the start holds of The Prow, finish The Prow.  

  Crux in the middle where it gets real thin, then crux again whilst trying to finish The Prow. Bring yo chalk bag.
content.protection: If you fall, you just step off. Pads only really needed for protecting the finish. 2 pads. 9 pads for gym rats.
content.location: Traverse from the right side of Warm-Up Wall (Porcelain Doll Wall) to the left, finish The Prow.

content.description:
Sit Start on good holds below the super obvious flake, climb up into the flake and dyno/deadpoint to the lip.

EDIT: As of Jan 2020, the flake that defined this problem has broken, leaving behind a decent edge as well as a deep undercling mono/shallow 2 finger pocket.

The climb has been re-sent using a left hand on the right hand pocket of the V2 to the left, right hand on the new edge and dyno to the top. Alternatively, this climb has also been redone utilizing the new undercling and a right hand Gaston to throw right hand to the lip. Both variations are approximately V4 and V3 respectively (McKinney grades).
content.location: Just right of "Another one worth doing"

content.description: Start sitting, climb through jugs and pockets into a sharp left hand undercling and awkward right hand 2 finger undercling. Use a left hand sprag (spock) to set your feet, readjust your right hand, and grab the lip. Pull an uncharacteristically hard top out for McKinney.
content.location: Starts around the same location as Snakebelly. Left of Adams Jump and Mono Pop.

content.description: Stand start on left sloper edge and a right shallow pocket, then dyno to the lip.  One move wonder.
content.location: 8 feet to the right of Another One Worth Doing; right of Mono Pop.

climbs.name: 5 Dope aka Another One Worth Doing (aka Shitty Warmup Right)

content.description: Stand start on jugs and move up into a good right pocket.  Make a large move onto another pocket (left) before popping to the top.  Crux is moving off the top pocket to the lip.
content.location: To the right of The Prow and Unknown V2 (aka Shitty Warmup Left).

content.description: Stand start on the big shelf.  Move into a left sloper and a right sloper crimp, and dyno to the top.  Crux is the dyno.
content.location: Located to the right of the Prow; on the big shelf.

content.description: The most popular spot at McKinney with The Prow being the highlight problem.
